generated_text:
Below is a structured HTML message alerting recipients to phishing attempts, including advice on safeguarding their online accounts.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Phishing Alert</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }
        p {
            color: #555;
        }
       .alert {
            background-color: #f8d7da;
            border: 1px solid #f5c6cb;
            border-radius: 5px;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
       .advice {
            background-color: #e4f0f2;
            border: 1px solid #bcd1c5;
            border-radius: 5px;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="alert">
        <h1>Phishing Alert</h1>
        <p>We have received reports of phishing attempts targeting our users. Phishing is a common technique used by cybercriminals to trick you into revealing personal information, such as passwords and credit card numbers.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="advice">
        <h2>How to Safeguard Your Online Accounts</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Never click on links or download attachments from unknown or suspicious sources.</li>
            <li>Be cautious of emails that appear to come from well-known companies but use generic email addresses.</li>
            <li>Use strong, unique passwords for each of your accounts.</li>
            <li>Enable two-factor authentication (2FA) whenever possible to add an extra layer of security.</li>
            <li>Be wary of emails that contain urgent calls to action or threaten consequences if you don’t act immediately.</li>
            <li>Keep your software and systems up to date to protect against the latest threats.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

This HTML message provides a clear alert about phishing attempts and offers practical advice to help recipients protect their online accounts.

